1.引入和分析数据¶

Wine-Reviews,winemag-data_first150k.csv CSV

Pandasread_csv()CSVDataFrame()DataFrame

Data Columns¶

  1. countryThe country that the wine is from
  2. description
  3. designationThe vineyard within the winery where the grapes that made the wine are from
  4. pointsThe number of points WineEnthusiast rated the wine on a scale of 1-100 (though they say they only post reviews for wines that score >=80)
  5. priceThe cost for a bottle of the wine
  6. provinceThe province or state that the wine is from
  7. region_1The wine growing area in a province or state (ie Napa)
  8. region_2Sometimes there are more specific regions specified within a wine growing area (ie Rutherford inside the Napa Valley), but this value can sometimes be blank
  9. varietyThe type of grapes used to make the wine (ie Pinot Noir)
  10. wineryThe winery that made the wine

#  Spearman
from scipy.stats import spearmanr
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.formula.api import ols

WinerDF_del = WinerDF.dropna(how="any", subset=["price"])
coef,p = spearmanr(WinerDF_del['points'], WinerDF_del['price'])
print('Spearmans : %.4f' % coef)
alpha = 0.05
if p > alpha:
    print(' (H0)')

else:
    print(' (rH0)')

 (rH0)

region = ''
ConProvDict={}
for row in region_null.itertuples():
    # 
    if len(ConProvDict) ==0:
        simTuple = WinerDF[(WinerDF.province==row[1])& (WinerDF.variety==row[2]) & ~(WinerDF.region_1.isnull())]['region_1']
        if len(simTuple)==0:
            simTuple = WinerDF[(WinerDF.province==row[1])& ~(WinerDF.region_1.isnull())]['region_1']
        
        # region_1
        if len(simTuple) ==0:
            simTuple = WinerDF[(WinerDF.country==row[3])& ~(WinerDF.region_1.isnull())]['region_1']
        if len(simTuple)==0:
            region = ''
            subDict = {row[2]:region}
            ConProvDict[row[1]]= subDict
        else:
            region = simTuple.value_counts().keys()[0]
            subDict = {row[2]:region}
            ConProvDict[row[1]]= subDict
            WinerDF[row[0]:row[0]+1]['region_1']= region   
    if ConProvDict.get(row[1])!=None and ConProvDict[row[1]].get(row[2])!=None:
        region = ConProvDict[row[1]][row[2]]
        if region !='':
             WinerDF[row[0]:row[0]+1]['region_1']= region
    else:
        simTuple = WinerDF[(WinerDF.province==row[1])& (WinerDF.variety==row[2]) & ~(WinerDF.region_1.isnull())]['region_1']
        if len(simTuple)==0:
            simTuple = WinerDF[(WinerDF.province==row[1])& ~(WinerDF.region_1.isnull())]['region_1']
        # region_1
        if len(simTuple) ==0:
            simTuple = WinerDF[(WinerDF.country==row[3])& ~(WinerDF.region_1.isnull())]['region_1']
        if len(simTuple)==0:
            region = ''
            subDict = {row[2]:region}
            ConProvDict[row[1]]= subDict
        else:
            region = simTuple.value_counts().keys()[0]
            subDict = {row[2]:region}
            ConProvDict[row[1]]= subDict
            WinerDF[row[0]:row[0]+1]['region_1']= region

WinerDFV2.reset_index(inplace=True,drop=True)

NoneRegionList = WinerDFV2New[WinerDFV2New['region_1'].isnull()][['region_1','title','province']]
print( len(NoneRegionList))
for row in NoneRegionList.itertuples():
    if row[2]!=None:
        result =re.search(r'[(](.*?)[)]',row[2])
        if result !=None:
            region = result.group().replace('(','').replace(')','')
            WinerDFV2New[row[0]:row[0]+1]['region_1'] = region
